{"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/37377", "repository_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust", "labels_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/37377/labels{/name}", "comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/37377/comments", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/37377/events", "html_url": "https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/issues/37377", "id": 184916302, "node_id": "MDU6SXNzdWUxODQ5MTYzMDI=", "number": 37377, "title": "Rust incorrectly coerces byte string literals", "user": {"login": "eugene2k", "id": 1811946, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjE4MTE5NDY=", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/1811946?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/eugene2k", "html_url": "https://github.com/eugene2k", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/eugene2k/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/eugene2k/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/eugene2k/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/eugene2k/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/eugene2k/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/eugene2k/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/eugene2k/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/eugene2k/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/eugene2k/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "labels": [], "state": "closed", "locked": false, "assignee": null, "assignees": [], "milestone": null, "comments": 2, "created_at": "2016-10-24T18:19:50Z", "updated_at": "2016-10-24T21:00:54Z", "closed_at": "2016-10-24T21:00:54Z", "author_association": "NONE", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "This code:\n\n```\nextern \"C\" {\n    fn puts(string: *const std::os::raw::c_char) -> std::os::raw::c_int;\n}\nfn main() {\n    [1,2,3] as *const u8;\n    b\"Hello\" as *const u8;\n    unsafe {\n        puts([1,2,3] as *const i8);\n        puts(b\"Hello\\0\" as *const i8);\n    }\n}\n```\n\nproduces these errors:\n\n```\nerror: non-scalar cast: `[i32; 3]` as `*const u8`\n --> src/main.rs:7:5\n  |\n7 |     [1,2,3] as *const u8;\n  |     ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^\n\nerror: non-scalar cast: `[i32; 3]` as `*const i8`\n  --> src/main.rs:10:14\n   |\n10 |         puts([1,2,3] as *const i8);\n   |              ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^\n\nerror[E0308]: mismatched types\n  --> src/main.rs:11:14\n   |\n11 |         puts(b\"Hello\\0\" as *const i8);\n   |              ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^ expected u8, found i8\n\nerror: aborting due to 3 previous errors\n```\n\nI'm not sure if it's supposed to be possible to cast byte string literals as *const ptrs, but when in the second call to `puts()` you try to cast b\"Helo\\0\" as u8 instead of i8, the error changes to \"exected i8, found u8\".\n\nTested on stable(1.12) and nightly(2016-10-21)\n", "closed_by": {"login": "eugene2k", "id": 1811946, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjE4MTE5NDY=", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/1811946?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/eugene2k", "html_url": "https://github.com/eugene2k", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/eugene2k/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/eugene2k/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/eugene2k/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/eugene2k/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/eugene2k/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/eugene2k/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/eugene2k/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/eugene2k/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/eugene2k/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "reactions": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/37377